cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.CC

This paper deals with the construction of codes for rank modulation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on the construction of snake-in-the-box codes, which are a type of combinatorial object (cs.DS) and are used in the realization of flash memories (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of Gray codes, which are commonly used in computer science and engineering (cs.SI), and the construction of longer snakes using previously known constructions (cs.CC).
